[[File:Ingazeira.jpg|thumb|left|240px|Ingazeira Overview]] [[File:Bandeira do Município de Ingazeira.jpg|thumb|right|160px|Ingazeira's City Flag]] '''Ingazeira''' is a city in the state of [[Pernambuco]], [[Brazil]]. The population in 2009, according with [[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|IBGE]] was 4.561 inhabitants and the total area is 243.67&nbsp;km².
==Geography==
* State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Sertão]] Pernambucano * Boundaries - [[São José do Egito]] and [[Tabira, Pernambuco|Tabira]] ('''N'''); [[Iguaraci]] ('''S''' and '''W'''); [[Tuparetama]] ('''E'''). * Area - 243.67&nbsp;km² * Elevation - 534 m * Hidrography - [[Pajeú River]] * Vegetation - [[Caatinga]] [[hiperxerófila]] * Clima - [[semi arid]] - ([[Sertão]]) hot * Annual average temperature - 23.8 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 372.5&nbsp;km
==Economy== [[File:Igreja Matriz de São José (5).jpg|thumb|right|220px|Saint Joseph Church]] The main economic activities in '''Ingazeira''' are based in [[agribusiness]], especially creation of [[sheep]], [[goat]]s, [[cattle]], [[chicken]]s; and plantations of [[maize|corn]], [[bean]]s and [[tomato]]es.
